## Widget Gallery Titles
accordion = Accordion
    .description = An accordion displays a list of headers that can be expanded one at a time to reveal content.
avatar = Avatar
    .description = An avatar is used to visually represent a person or entity and can contain text, an icon, or an image.
avatar-group = Avatar Group
    .description = An avatar group displays multiple avatars stacked together to represent a collection of users or entities.
badge = Badge
    .description = A badge is used to highlight an item's status, category, or count. Badges can contain text, numbers, or icons, and may be styled with semantic colour variants.
button-title = Button
    .description = A button can be used to send an event when pressed. Typically they are used to trigger an action.
calendar = Calendar
    .description = A calendar allows users to select dates and navigate through months and years.
card = Card
    .description = A card is a surface that groups related content and actions on a single topic.
chip = Chip
    .description = A chip can be used to inform the user of the status of specific data.
collapsible = Collapsible
    .description = A collapsible shows or hides its content when the header is pressed.
combobox = Combobox
    .description = A combobox combines a text input with a list of options.
divider = Divider
    .description = A divider is a line that separates content into distinct sections.
dropdown = Dropdown
    .description = A dropdown displays a list of options that can be opened and closed.
element = Element
    .description = Element is a bare-bones view with no built-in content. It is a flexible building block for custom layouts, decorative shapes, and styled placeholder regions.
grid = Grid
    .description = A grid arranges children into rows and columns defined by explicit track sizes.
hstack = HStack
    .description = The hstack container can be used to layout views in a row.
image = Image
    .description = An image view displays an image from the resource manager.
knob = Knob
    .description = A knob is a rotary control that allows users to select a value.
label = Label
    .description = A label can be used to display a string of text.
list = List
    .description = A list displays items in a scrollable container.
markdown = Markdown
    .description = The Markdown view renders a subset of Markdown inline within the UI.
menu = Menu
    .description = A menu displays a list of options that can be selected.
menu-bar = MenuBar
    .description = A menu bar contains multiple menu items for navigation and actions.
popover = Popover
    .description = A popover displays floating content anchored to a trigger element. It closes when focus moves outside.
progress-bar = ProgressBar
    .description = A progress bar shows the progress of a process or task.
radiobutton = Radio Button
    .description = A radio button can be used to select an option from a set of options.
rating = Rating
    .description = A rating control allows users to rate items on a scale.
resizable = Resizable
    .description = A resizable wraps a view with a draggable handle that lets the user change its size. Double-click the handle to reset.
scrollview = Scrollview
    .description = A scrollview provides a scrollable area for its content.
select = Select
    .description = A view which allows the user to select an option from a list.
slider = Slider
    .description = A slider allows the user to select a value from a continuous range by dragging a thumb along a track.
spinbox = Spinbox
    .description = A spinbox allows users to select a numeric value by clicking increment/decrement buttons or typing.
switch = Switch
    .description = A switch toggles between two states.
svg = Svg
    .description = An SVG view displays scalable vector graphics.
tabview = TabView
    .description = A tabview displays multiple tabs that can be switched between.
table = Table
    .description = A table displays tabular data with sortable, resizable columns and row selection. Click a column header to sort. Click a row to select it.
toggle-button = Toggle Button
    .description = A toggle button switches between two states when clicked.
tooltip = Tooltip
    .description = A tooltip displays supplemental information near its target view. Tooltips are triggered on hover or focus of the target view and dismissed on blur or mouse-out of the target or tooltip container.
virtual-list = Virtual List
    .description = A virtual list only renders visible items, keeping memory and render cost low for large datasets.
virtual-table = VirtualTable
    .description = A virtual table renders only the visible rows for large datasets, keeping memory and render cost low. This demo shows 500 rows.
xypad = XYPad
    .description = An XYPad provides a 2D input surface for controlling two values simultaneously by dragging.
vstack = VStack
    .description = The vstack container can be used to layout views in a column.
zstack = ZStack
    .description = The zstack container can be used to layer views on top of each other.
markdown-rendering = Markdown Rendering
basic-table = Basic Table
virtual-table-500-row = 500-row VirtualTable

## Accordion Content
accordion-item-what-is-vizia-title = What is Vizia?
accordion-item-what-is-vizia-body = Vizia is a declarative GUI framework for building desktop applications in Rust.
accordion-item-style-views-title = How do I style views?
accordion-item-style-views-body = Use CSS-like stylesheets and class selectors to customize the appearance of views.
accordion-item-reactive-title = Is Vizia reactive?
accordion-item-reactive-body = Yes! Vizia uses reactive signals so the UI updates automatically when data changes.

